Terris - Thule<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufazdaar00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fazdaar00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/01 6:45:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Settle down</span><hr size=1> Geeze Samadhi BoTS, take a chill pill. I don't know about you, but myself and many others consider Grimstaff an excellent source of info and insights into the wizard class. He never makes personal attacks, which you seem to actively participate in, you never back up what you say with numbers, only anecdotes (sp?). He shows the numbers, and all you do is say he is wrong and wizards have no problems. If you believe the class has no problems, just go play it. Others are trying to get some positive changes toward the class. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugherad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gherad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/01 12:07:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Settle down</span><hr size=1> Fazdaar00,<br>
<br>
Grimstaff is a passionate and dedicated defender of the wizard class.  I'm glad he cares so much and tries so hard to get us improved.  But there is no substitute for experience.  I'm sure he is an excellent wizard, but he has always been 10 levels behind the curve and so has always fought for lower level wizards.<br>
<br>
Samadhi and the other level 60 wizards know a heck of a lot more about the high level game.  You shouldn't be so quick to discount their insights.<br>
<br>
Should Verant make efforts to balance all the classes at every single level? Of course.  Is it going to happen?  No way.<br>
<br>
So while Grimstaff or other discontented wizards can always find numbers that show that a level 44 wizard is weaker than a 44 mage, or a level 8 cleric nukes more than a level 8 wizard, such facts do little to explain how the game is actually played.<br>
<br>
Some of the level 60 folks have indeed posted numbers comparing rogue damage to wizard damage.  The choice to ignore those numbers was yours.<br>
<br>
&quot;Others are trying to get some positive changes toward the class. &quot;<br>
<br>
The rest of us are trying to explain how things really are and share our experiences (good or bad).  Since hundreds of wizards will read this thread and probably zero Verant employees, you tell me which is more productive <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/01 12:29:14 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Experience?</span><hr size=1> Actually since I have 85 days played and started in June of 1999, I'd say I have a bit of experience.  More than most of the level 60 Wizards in play at present, actually, since many of them shot up levels very rapidly through quad kiting and such.  I have spent a good 50% of my time exploring, experimenting, helping people, and learning.  So I would have to say the 'lack of experience' line is a bit off base.<br>
<br>
And as for being 10 levels out of touch... from whom?  From people who are level 60?  That's an odd statement, it makes it sound like there is a baseline of Wizards that I have been consistently lower level than and there is no such thing.  I have a good memory for what I went through as a lower level Wizard, unlike, apparently, many high level wizards.  I understand what it was like, and while it is hard to believe, numbers aren't relative.  If a blast at level 1 does less damage than another blast, then it does.  Game play or not, it really DOES do that less damage.<br>
<br>
But the reason I bring this kind of thing up isn't so much to get the damage raised (although that would be good) its to point out a design and conceptual flaw with Verant and how they put the Wizard class together.  It is my firm contention that when the spell design guys lowered Wizard power after beta, they lowered it without being properly in context with the other caster classes.  In other words, when they lowered Shock of Frost to 6 points of damage, they didnt pay attention to the fact that Strike does 8 damage.  When they lowered Ice Shock to 320 damage, they didn't pay attention to the fact that Cinder Bolt does 333 damage.<br>
<br>
They didn't consider the effect of a class wholely reliant on blasts getting only one highly resisted and HUGELY aggroing blast at level 20, then a gain of only 9 points of damage 4 levels later (actually starts out lower damage).<br>
<br>
They didn't consider how much the failure of sight spells to compensate for the lacking of the Wizard class was going to impact actual play.<br>
<br>
They didn't fully and properly think through how poorly shadowstep etc and root would compensate for having no pet, nor AC/HP/combat skills of melee characters (especially after heavily nerfing fades and nerfing root).<br>
<br>
In other words, Verant wasn't being careful nor very thoughtful when they 'finished' the Wizard class, and if they WERE thoughtful, then they would see and understand what needs to be done better.  And as for the concept that we'd solo better with better damage at these levels... if it is acceptible for a Cleric - with better AC, combat skills, weapons, the ability to heal and buff - to do 41 damage to ANY target at level 5 (vs undead), why is it unacceptible for Wizards to do this damage, given their limitations and intended class design.<br>
<br>
So if you think about it a little while, you'll see it isn't about damage, it isn't about making Wizards kewl d00ds like Raistlin and Picolo or whatever his name is.  It is about getting Verant to be consistent, thoughtful, and to consider the design concept of the class more completely.<br>
<br>
Of course, I consider it to be too late now, that Verant will do no such thing, because it would take too much work.  That is despite the fact that it's pretty unanimous among other classes that Wizards are most in need of a look. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubethude.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bethude</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/01 12:29:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Settle down</span><hr size=1> *looks around for all these numbers that grim has*<br>
